result.execSummary:
Gary Lee Bodie was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Gary Lee Bodie was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Gary Lee Bodie

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Gary Lee Bodie in court, in custody.  Bruce Poquette appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant acknowledges receipt of complaint tendered by the District Attorney.  Court advised the defendant as to his rights.  Defendant does not wish to have an atty and admits he is the person wanted from  DeKalb County Georgia.  Wishes to waive extradition.  Court finds defendant has freely waived his right and does waive extradition.  Defendant signs waiver.   Court signs document.  Remanded to the Sheriff's Department to await Georgia picking up the defendant.
